snippet.textDisplay: Gravity and subatomic interactions will not be constant due to variations is velocity/vector within an atom.  When thinking about items which exist within "finite" points in space they actually fluctuate within an atomic gradient which could be measured as random.  If those points are within that gradient then they will seem random since the vector of each item within the atom will vary greatly.  However when you reach the upper and lower bounds of that gradient then the ratio will overcome the chaos previously seen.
